57: Funding Proposal - Elk-Symmetric comarketing 2

Background:

Elk finance was just rewarded $125,000 in $STAKE rewards to incentives liquidity providers and thus liquidity flow to xdai. Elk is a burn and mint bridge migrating to decentralized node operators which allows liquidity flow from any of the networks they are currently operating on over a dozen supported networks including; ftm, matic, avax, bsc, moonriver, xdai and many others. Elk is using the $STAKE rewards as an opportunity to ignite some cross marketing exposure by asking protocols if they are interested in partnering in this program. This proposal is to authorize $5000 in community funds to be spent on Symmetric’s involvement with this program.

Purpose:
The elk-symm pair has the potential to bring volume to the symm token with very little incentives due to the piggy backing off the $125k stake rewards. symm would provide $5k in rewards, elk matches, symmetric would get exposure from 12-15 networks, co-marketing alongside other xdai projects, and an AMA. This would also give us an opportunity to build a relationship with ELK that could go cross chain. Since ELK is on more than a dozen evm chains any chains Symmetric is on or goes to we could leverage ELK to create a mutually beneficial relationship we could also work to have them add CELO.

Additional background:

snapshot.org

Snapshot

Timeline:

Sharing of comarketing will occur in advance share all potential partners involved.

1.) On Wednesday Nov 17 farms will go live, including Symm-Elk
2.) The Symm-Elk pair will be rewarded with the additional Symm rewards described below approximately November 30th
3.) An AMA with ELK community will take place after Farms launch to educate the ELK and Symmetric community on the farms and the protocol.
4.) dual rewards will extend for months for duration of funds and may receive additional boost from ELK depending on trading volume from partnered pairs

Funding Information:

Amount of Symm tokens requested: ~ $5000 in Symm fund the ELK-Symm pair at a rate of 200% APR (approximately 2 months)

Retroactive Billing for ‘What is a DAO?’

Hey Everyone,

This is my first funding type post on Discourse, so please let me know if there’s any valuable information missing.

Just a heads up, because this sort of grew out of an internal DAOhaus project, the billing gets sort of messy. Here’s how we arrived at this price:

tldr

5,700 WXDAI to Splainer DAO treasury

Address on XDAI: 0xad80fbdb9c9652b5238dbd1dc4b4c7f7c364dba7

We took a good chunk off the price because there was stuff MageSmiths was already billed for + a general friends and family discount + it took longer to make this than it should have.

The Breakdown

Usually, a first video is pretty pricey because:

  • There would be a lot of research to write the script (not in this case, but worth mentioning)
  • Meetings after meetings to concept and establish tone. Essential to get a consistent character throughout each department of production.
  • New animation styles and workflows to match that new tone.

However, things are different in this case

  • Much of the concept work happened in DAOhaus with Ven helping out a lot
  • Adrienne had already billed MageSmiths for around 2,500 for this project.
  • We didn’t need to do research.

All considered, 9k is what would we thought would be a fair overall price, minus what Adrienne already billed for, minus a fee for taking forever, minus a DH ‘friends and family’ discount, we arrive at 5.5k + the VO KromNom had paid for out of pocket, which was 251 CAD, which rounds nicely to 200 USD at current rates.

9,000 total
(- 500 DH ‘friends & family’)
(- 500 Sloth tax)
(- 2, 500, billed already)
(+ 200 voiceover)
__
5,500

Rough Estimate For Future Episodes

Considering that the tone and style is established, future episodes will require far less pre-production. We have animation workflows now and can make better decisions about the cost/benefits of adding in certain elements.

We can expect the future cost to be around 7.5k for an episode of similar quality and length.

Perhaps more importantly, we know what it takes to make Splainers now. We’ve refined a workflow, and we’re starting to train apprentices (if anyone else is interested, let us know in our Discord), so turn-around times are going to be way faster as we get things in motion.

If you have any questions or concerns, please let me know in the comments.

Jord

53: Signal Proposal - Bounties for NEAR network

Initial feedback from the community is supportive of deploying Symmetric to more networks beyond xDai and Celo.

The protocol itself (smart contracts) will be covered by operations to ensure they are securely handled.

However, we want to give the wider community the opportunity to participate in the wider deployment of Symmetric to these new networks through a series of bounties. If these bounties are not picked up then they will be scheduled in the future to be covered by the core team as part of the sprint planning process.

This bounty is specifically for the NEAR network and covers the following.

ExchangeUI – 200 SYMM
PoolsUI – 200 SYMM
Subgraph – 75 SYMM
Symmetric.Assets – 75 SYMM
SOR (Smart Object Router) – 75 SYMM
IPFS-Push – 50 SYMM
Mining script – 50 SYMM

These are the projects that need to be updated to allow Symmetric to run on the target network. Smart contracts and other tasks would be covered by the core team.

44: Signal Proposal - Extra reward payment on Celo to correct for Coingecko misreporting bug

Symmetric’s reward script uses Coingecko to retrieve SYMM price when calculating reward payments. For one week, Coingecko had a bug where it wasn’t updating SYMM price correctly which means the payout was too low on Celo.

We’ve calculated that if it was correct then rewards on Celo for that one week would be roughly double. This vote is to approve an additional payment on Celo to correct that reward payout.

The total correction is 334.901722503104 SYMM split across all LP’s on Celo.

43: Signal Proposal - Extra payment to stable pool on xDai for incorrect APR reporting

The dashboard was incorrectly reporting APR’s for the WXDAI/USDC pool on xDai up to the 7th October. This is because it wasn’t applying the hard pegged penalty although the reward payout did apply this penalty correctly. This means the reward payout was correct but the dashboard was incorrect.

But users were using the APR being displayed in the dashboard when deciding to load liquidity and so we feel that we should honour what was displayed in the dashboard which means calculating what would have been paid out if the hard penalty wasn’t applied and making an additional payment of the difference between what was paid and what was expected by users.

We have calculated this already and it comes to a total payout of 248.848437377482 SYMM covering from when the pool was created on the 9th August through to when the dashboard was corrected on the 7th October.

This vote is whether to proceed with this correction payout.
